noun.description: A gill of a fish. Usually in plural.

verb.description: To tickle (a fish, a fish's gills or belly); to catch (fish, especially trout) by tickling the gills or belly. Also without object: to hunt (for fish) in this way with the hands, or with a small loop attached to a stick.

origin: Late 15th century; earliest use found in Catholicon Anglicum: an English-Latin wordbook. Origin unknown<br>early 19th century; earliest use found in John Rennie (1761–1821), engineer. From ginnle.
